❤️Adopted❤️Sharing again for this sweet senior!!! Capullo, #A3660692, is an 11 year old chihuahua/Jack Russell terrier mix who is having a hard time at the shelter. He is scared and confused in his kennel but once he gets out he transforms into an affectionate, happy, fun little guy. Who would guess he is a senior the way he zooms around the play yard? He loves attention, gets along with other small dogs and has the softest fur and the cutest underbite ever!! Capullo would love to find a quiet adult only home where he can be loved and adored for the amazing boy that he is! Please don’t let him languish another day in his cold kennel. Come meet this charming little guy at: Castaic Shelter, 31044 N. Charlie Canyon Rd, Castaic, Ca 91384. Hours: Mon-Thurs 12-7 and Fri-Sun 10-5 Closed Holidays (661) 257-3191

Please Help sweet senior Bogart find adoption or rescue by sharing!! 💗

Bogart is a 12 year old Poodle mix. This old boy has lost his sight, but his sniffer still works, and his tail still wags. Bogart needs a safe, quiet home where he can feel secure and live out his senior years. He also has some dental issues that need attention. Otherwise, he’s a low stress companion who spends most of his time resting quietly. He has been at the shelter since Dec 20th and weighs 13 pounds.
*Come visit Bogart at the shelter or contact Tiffani at tiffani.hamilton@lacity.org or 213-435-2238 (city cell) to help! *

Meet Mellie! She is an adorable and tiny 4 month old crosseyed cutie. Mellie can see just fine but her wonky eye just makes her even cuter, and gives her the special talent of being able to keep an eye on the toy and an eye on you at the same time! She's a sweet girl who loves to play with other cats and kittens and will settle down for a snuggle as well. She may be young enough to learn to like dogs too. Contact Goodmewsrescue@gmail.com to meet Mellie.

.
Así es como reacciona un animal que ha recibido amor. Le encanta jugar, que lo acaricien y compartir tiempo con su dueño. .
.
.Los animales que ves en la calle, gatos o perros, aquellos que son temerosos y huyen cuando te acercas, o aquellos que te muestran sus dientes o garras como señal de defensa, son animales que han sufrido de abandono, maltrato e indiferencia.
No te dejes confundir, esa no es su verdadera naturaleza. Ningún animal nace siendo malo o agresivo, llega a serlo por las circunstancias y su entorno. .
.
.
Así que la próxima vez, no lo espantes o le temas. Piensa qué puedes hacer para evitar que más animales corran ese mismo destino. -

Where Are They Now?

Previously known as Baby Boy, Momo is fulfilling his mission of becoming the most spoiled kitty of 2018 in his forever home! "Momo has settled in wonderfully with our little family. He loves to carry around and play with a little stuffed mouse that we bought him, as well as any of the yarn that’s laying around our house. To say the least, Momo has pretty much taken over the whole house with his Momo-ness. From the way that he talks to us, like he is either asking us what we are doing or where we are to laying on our faces when we are napping (see picture). He enjoys watching my boyfriend play videogames, climbing his kitty tree, and watching our neighbors every move. "Attached are some pictures of him being a shoulder kitty (his favorite spot to sit), him stealing the show in the pictures we put in our Christmas cards, and him deciding that it is a wonderful idea to nap on the face of someone else napping."
